# Wolfram-Alignment Tiebreaker

When multiple design or implementation options are viable:

1. **Prefer the option that best aligns with Wolfram Physics Project philosophy**: causality as fundamental; space and time as emergent from causal structure; propagation (e.g. C) as a property of causal rules, not of space.
2. **If more than one option aligns**, prefer the one that is **computationally simpler or faster**, so long as it still respects (1).

Do not choose a faster/simpler option that inverts or weakens the causality-first ontology (e.g. treating space as primary and propagation as a spatial property) unless there is a compelling practical constraint that cannot be satisfied otherwise.
